---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Digital resilience | Cello"
	description="Practical visibility, security, automation and assurance options for the systems that depend on Cello networks."
>
	<section class="page-hero">
		<div class="page-hero-inner narrow">
			<p class="eyebrow">Digital resilience</p>
			<h1>Act on risk before it becomes disruption.</h1>
			<p class="lead">
				Cello's network foundation can now extend into clearer visibility, stronger
				control and faster response across the systems that keep enterprise teams
				operating under pressure.
			</p>
			<div class="actions">
				<a class="button dark" href="/contact">Start a conversation</a>
				<a class="button dark" href="/solutions/smartwan">Back to networks</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section topology">
		<div class="section-header">
			<div>
				<p class="eyebrow">Four capability areas</p>
				<h2>Clarity across complex environments.</h2>
			</div>
			<p class="lead">
				The language is calm and practical: see what matters, protect critical
				paths, automate repeatable response and evidence resilience for leaders,
				auditors and customers.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="capability-grid">
			<div class="tile">
				<h3>Observability</h3>
				<p>Unify telemetry across applications, infrastructure and services so teams can investigate the unknown.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tile">
				<h3>Security and cyber defence</h3>
				<p>Make security telemetry reliable, actionable and integrated with broader operational context.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tile">
				<h3>Automation</h3>
				<p>Reduce repetitive work and accelerate response through practical orchestration.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="tile">
				<h3>Compliance and assurance</h3>
				<p>Design evidence-ready architectures that help teams show control, not just claim it.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="split">
			<div class="copy">
				<p class="eyebrow">Start focused</p>
				<h2>Bounded work, useful outputs, clear next step.</h2>
				<p>
					Cello can help customers strengthen digital resilience through reliable
					connectivity, clearer visibility and accountable support around the
					network services they already depend on.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Understand where signal quality, value or cost confidence is weak.</li>
					<li>Prioritise improvements by business value and operational risk.</li>
					<li>Leave teams with evidence they can use internally.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="ink-panel">
				<p class="eyebrow">Customer promise</p>
				<p class="quote">
					When pressure rises, teams need a clearer picture and enough confidence
					to make the next decision well.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="section-header">
			<div>
				<p class="eyebrow">How it fits Cello</p>
				<h2>More value around the same trusted relationship.</h2>
			</div>
			<p class="lead">
				For Cello clients, the benefit is a broader operating view from the
				partner already accountable for critical connectivity.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="process">
			<div class="process-item">
				<h3>Current picture</h3>
				<p>Start with the environment, pressures and systems the team already knows.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="process-item">
				<h3>Signal quality</h3>
				<p>Find where data, alerts or visibility do not support confident decisions.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="process-item">
				<h3>Practical path</h3>
				<p>Prioritise fixes by effort, value, cost and risk.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="process-item">
				<h3>Operate better</h3>
				<p>Improve detection, response and assurance over time.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="cta">
		<div>
			<p class="eyebrow">Digital resilience</p>
			<h2>Build confidence around the network.</h2>
			<p>Use visibility, security and automation to support the systems your business relies on.</p>
		</div>
		<a class="button" href="/contact">Talk to Cello</a>
	</section>
</Layout>
